theorem Topology.interior_closure_union_subset_union_interior_closure {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (closure ((A ∪ B) : Set X)) ⊆
      interior (closure A) ∪ interior (closure B) := by
  intro x hx
  -- Rewrite `closure (A ∪ B)` as `closure A ∪ closure B`.
  have hx' : (x : X) ∈ interior (closure A ∪ closure B) := by
    simpa [closure_union] using hx
  -- Use `interior_union` to split the interior of the union.
  have hx'' : (x : X) ∈ interior (closure A) ∪ interior (closure B) := by
    simpa [interior_union] using hx'
  exact hx''

theorem Topology.interior_closure_union_subset_union_closure {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (closure ((A ∪ B) : Set X)) ⊆
      closure (A : Set X) ∪ closure B := by
  intro x hx
  -- From `hx`, we know `x` lies in the closure of `A ∪ B`.
  have h_cl : (x : X) ∈ closure ((A ∪ B) : Set X) :=
    interior_subset hx
  -- Rewrite the closure of a union as the union of the closures.
  -- This turns the goal into exactly the membership we already have.
  simpa [closure_union] using h_cl
